<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900806-0063</DOCNO><DOCID>900806-0063.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Mesa Limited Partnership:   Concern Reports Net Loss   Widened in Second Quarter</HL><DATE>08/06/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A7A</SO><CO>   MLP</CO><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)SECURITIES INDUSTRY (SCR)</IN><LP>   Mesa Limited Partnership, Dallas, citing disappointingprices for natural gas, said its net loss widened in thesecond quarter to $50 million, or 49 cents a unit, from $13.4million, or one cent a unit, a year earlier.   T. Boone Pickens, the company's general partner, said Mesaexpects a 1990 average gas price of $1.60 per 1,000 cubicfeet this year. In the latest quarter, prices fell to $1.39per 1,000 cubic feet from $1.56 a year earlier.</LP><TEXT>   Revenue fell to $62.3 million from $83.3 million.   Results from the latest quarter included losses totaling$6.9 million from securities transactions and from the saleof oil and gas properties. The year-ago figure included $23.9million in gains from similar transactions.   For the first half, Mesa reported a net loss of $68.2million, or 79 cents a unit, on revenue of $158.8 million,against profit of $1.2 million, or 14 cents a unit, onrevenue of $188.4 million, a year earlier.</TEXT></DOC>